<span id="freeTextContainer17227239453995324378">The Polar Express automatically gets 5 stars just for its simple cozy factor. I mean can it be any more winter vibe, let&apos;s get in the holiday mood, I can&apos;t wait to ride the train scenario?<br/><br/>I&apos;ve seen the movie many times, not only in the theater but on a snowy evening bundled up with the kids. Somehow I never (embarrassingly) got around to reading the book. The prose is elegant and the illustrations soothing. <br/><br/>A little boy contemplates if Santa exists and all it takes is a ride on the Polar Express</span>
  <span id="freeText17227239453995324378" style="display:none">The Polar Express automatically gets 5 stars just for its simple cozy factor. I mean can it be any more winter vibe, let's get in the holiday mood, I can't wait to ride the train scenario?<br /><br />I've seen the movie many times, not only in the theater but on a snowy evening bundled up with the kids. Somehow I never (embarrassingly) got around to reading the book. The prose is elegant and the illustrations soothing. <br /><br />A little boy contemplates if Santa exists and all it takes is a ride on the Polar Express to find the truth. But the truth is hidden for only those that believe. <br /><br />The last page of the book includes a little surprise; a keepsake ornament inscribed with "All Aboard". My daughter loved every minute of The Polar Express. I especially liked the detailed writing that helped to awaken her imagination. </span>
