<div id="review_1946271211" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1946271211" />
    <a title="Andrew" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/800291-andrew"><img alt="Andrew" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1295167791p2/800291.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1946271211?book_show_action=true">Sep 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andrew" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andrew" href="/user/show/800291-andrew">Andrew</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781842709498" href="/book/show/9022655-the-polar-express">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1946271211" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer795606980219640880">I have been wanting to read this book for some time - if for nothing else but for the amazing artwork that Chris Van Allsburg created for this book. This is the sort of children&apos;s picture book I am sure would have got me hooked on reading at a much earlier age - the artwork is both so easy on the eye and yet has a mystical quality I cannot quite put my finger on. <br/><br/>what is more is this the man who illustrated Jamanji and Zathura so you can tell there is serious imagination behind each image and I </span>
  <span id="freeText795606980219640880" style="display:none">I have been wanting to read this book for some time - if for nothing else but for the amazing artwork that Chris Van Allsburg created for this book. This is the sort of children's picture book I am sure would have got me hooked on reading at a much earlier age - the artwork is both so easy on the eye and yet has a mystical quality I cannot quite put my finger on. <br /><br />what is more is this the man who illustrated Jamanji and Zathura so you can tell there is serious imagination behind each image and I love it. <br /><br />Yes it maybe a little early but you know when everything going on a little Christmas magic cannot be a bad thing and you know what I feel better for it. So yes a great book even about just over 30 pages and just what I needed too. <br /><br />The problem now is I want to go shopping for more of his books - oh well...</span>
  <a data-text-id="795606980219640880" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
